  "text": "Trace TLS connection chain from networking to crypto layers. The chain starts at netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpConnection.h (nsHttpConnection) which manages HTTP connections over TCP. Connection info flows through nsHttpConnectionInfo. The SSL/TLS integration point is security/manager/ssl/nsNSSIOLayer.h which defines nsSSLIOLayerHelpers (TLS intolerance handling, cipher config). NSSSocketControl (security/manager/ssl/NSSSocketControl.h) bridges NSS socket state. nsNSSIOLayer.cpp sets up the PSM IO layer. The low-level NSS crypto lives in security/nss/lib/ssl/: sslsecur.c handles SSL_ForceHandshake and DoRecv, ssl3con.c implements the TLS 3.x handshake state machine, sslimpl.h defines sslSecurityInfo struct, and tls13con.c handles TLS 1.3 specifics. Note: nsSSLIOLayerHelpers is in security/manager/ssl/ (not netwerk/socket/), and there is no standalone TLSFilterTransaction class file.",
